### Prompt Philosophy (Updated March 2026)

The category vision prompt operates as a **vibrational activation engine**, not a light polish:

1. **Declares, never asks** — No questions, no wondering, no "what if"
2. **Present tense only** — Everything IS. Not "will be", "I want", "someday"
3. **Obliterates weak language** — Comparison, hedging, seeking, past-reference → all transformed
4. **Preserves their specifics** — Names, places, activities, real details stay
5. **Transforms their voice** — Takes their content and makes it sound like someone who already HAS this life
6. **Ends with power** — Every category closes with a mic-drop sentence, not a trailing question

The imagination starter follows the same rules. No draft mentality, no "leave room for expansion",
no questions embedded in the text.
